text: Hester Jasper (born 7 May 2001) is a Dutch volleyball player. She played for the Dutch national team at the 2019 Nations League tournament. She started her career at VC Sneek in 2016. She moved to the German Bundesliga club VfB 91 Suhl in 2019. == References == == Other websites == * Profile at VfB Suhl * Profile at the German Volleyball Bundesliga (VBL) * Profile with the European Volleyball Association CEV Category:2001 births Category:Living people Category:Dutch volleyball players Category:Sportspeople from Friesland
